                      Friends believe in music ...                    Originally conceived as an event to celebrate 91.9 Friends FMs first anniversary on February 2008, Friends Music Festival has grown to become a popular calendar event for the citys music lovers. Commencing today, the third edition of the festival showcases various genres of music including Rabindrasangeet, Indian classical, folk, Bangla adhunik, Bangla rock and fusion. It also serves as a platform for loyal Friends listeners to witness live performances by their favourite musicians. Besides, audiences will also have the opportunity to get a glimpse of their favourite RJs, Ryan, Raja, Radhica, Nilanjana and Amit, who will be hosting the show over the next three days. To keep the festive mood alive, there will also be various food stalls, music stalls and other exhibitors participating at the event. Featuring performances by Madhuri- Shantiniketan, Srikanta Acharya, Rezwana Chowdhury Bannya, Baul Tarun Khyapa, Bickram Ghoshs Rhythmscape amp; Greg Ellis (today); Subhamita, Raghab, Dohar, Lopamudra Mitra, Purbayan Chatterjee amp; Anindo Chatterjee (tomorrow); Usha Uthup, Chandrabindoo, Nachiketa, Lakkhichhara and Bhoomi (December 6).                  Event: Friends Music Festival When: December 4 - 6; 5 pm onwards Where: Nazrul Mancha	                    
	Art      Till December 5 at Aakriti Art Gallery, 12/3A Hungerford Street, 3027/5041; 12 noon - 7 pm: Times Whirlwind  Art of Satish Gujral.     Till December 5 at Chemould Art Gallery, 12F Park Street; 2 pm - 7 pm: Paintings by Nihar Dey, Sanjoy Banerjee, Shibnath Mondal and Sambhu Nath Jana.     Till December 6 at Taj Bengal Promenade Lounge: Celebrating Love  paintings by Dhiren Sasmal, based on the love theme found in ancient classics of Bengali literature.     Till December 6 at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 4 pm - 8 pm: Dreamer Group presents an exhibition of drawings, paintings and sculptures by Bidyut Basak, Jagannath Sarkar, Kiran Kumar Sen, Lalit Maity, Manash Biswas, Purnandu Dey, Pradip Pradhan, Pradip Maity, Ranu Misra Banerjee, Rajib Deyashi, Saktipada Jana, Swapan Jana, Tapan Kar and Tarun Kumar Pal.     
